                         {
                          "content": "Now I can see the issue. Looking at the test that's timing out (`test_tokenize_basic` at line 442), it's processing a string with specific content. Let me examine the regex patterns in the `tokenize_source` function more closely.\n\nThe issue is in the regex patterns at lines 363-364 in `python_edit.py`:\n\n```python\nstring_patterns = ['\"(?:[^\"\\\\\\\\]|\\\\\\\\.)*?\"', \"'(?:[^'\\\\\\\\]|\\\\\\\\.)*?'\"]\n```\n\nThese regex patterns are using backtracking and can cause catastrophic backtracking in certain cases. The pattern `(?:[^\"\\\\\\\\]|\\\\\\\\.)*?` is particularly problematic because it has overlapping alternatives that can cause exponential time complexity with certain inputs.\n\nLet me check what specific input is causing the timeout:",
