                                                                                                     {
                                                                                                      "content": "## Progress Report\n\nI've been investigating the timeout issue in the `test_python_edit.py` tests, specifically in the `test_tokenize_basic` function. Here's what I've found and done:\n\n### Issue Identified\nThe timeout is occurring in the `tokenize_source` function at line 366 of `python_edit.py`, where a regex pattern is being used to match string literals. The regex patterns were using catastrophic backtracking, which can cause exponential time complexity with certain inputs.\n\n### Actions Taken\n1. **Updated the regex patterns for string matching** (line ~363):\n   - Changed from: `'\"(?:[^\"\\\\\\\\]|\\\\\\\\.)*?\"'` \n   - To: `'\"[^\"\\\\]*(?:\\\\.[^\"\\\\]*)*\"'`\n   - This pattern is more efficient and avoids catastrophic backtracking\n\n2. **Updated the triple quote patterns** (line ~331):\n   - Changed from: `'\"\"\"(?:[^\"\\\\\\\\]|\\\\\\\\.)*?\"\"\"'`\n   - To: `'\"\"\"[^\"\\\\]*(?:(?:\\\\.|\"(?!\"\"))[^\"\\\\]*)*\"\"\"'`\n\n### Current Status\nDespite these changes, the timeout is still occurring. When I tested the regex patterns in isolation, they work fine and execute instantly. However, when running the actual `tokenize_source` function, it still times out.\n\n### Next Steps\nThe issue appears to be more complex than just the regex patterns. I need to:\n1. Look for other potential infinite loops or performance issues in the `tokenize_source` function\n2. Check if there's an issue with how the patterns are being applied in the while loops\n3. Consider if there's a specific edge case in the test input that's causing the problem\n\nThe timeout suggests there might be an infinite loop somewhere in the tokenization logic, possibly in one of the while loops that processes matches.",
