                  "content": "\n        1:Work Order for python_edit.py Implementation\n        2:Files:\n        3:- bots/tools/python_edit.py: Main implementation\n        4:- tests/test_python_edit.py: Test suite\n        5:Current Status:\n        6:- Fixed infinite loop in tokenize_source that was causing test timeouts\n        7:- Issue was tokens being created with quotes, causing regex to match them again\n        8:- Fixed by removing quotes from token format in create_token()\n        9:- Fixed tokenization of inline comments\n        10:- Removed condition that prevented tokenizing comments on lines with tokens\n        11:- Preserved exact spacing between code and inline comments\n        12:- Fixed line insertion functionality\n        13:- Updated _handle_insertion to detokenize lines before comparison\n        14:- Correctly insert new AST nodes at the right position in the function body\n        15:- Fixed scope-based insertion (test_insert_after_scope)\n        16:- Added logic to handle inserting after a child scope when at parent level\n        17:- 37 tests passing (up from 34), 6 tests failing (down from 9)\n        18:Completed:\n        19:- Basic tokenization system working correctly\n        20:- Token system uses hex-encoded content with format: '__TOKEN__hexcontent__'\n        21:- Successfully handles:\n        22:- Basic expressions\n        23:- Comments (inline and standalone)\n        24:- String literals (single and multi-line)\n        25:- Nested structures\n        26:- Complex indentation\n        27:- Line insertion after specific lines now works\n        28:- Can insert code after comments\n        29:- Preserves indentation at function level\n        30:- Handles tokenized content correctly\n        31:- Scope-based insertion now works\n        32:- Can insert after 'OuterClass::another_method' when editing 'OuterClass'\n        33:- Properly finds child nodes and inserts after them\n        34:Remaining Issues:\n        35:1. Nested indentation for line insertion (test_line_insert_indentation)\n        36:   - When inserting after a line inside nested blocks (if/for/while)\n        37:   - Currently inserts at function level, not at the correct nesting level\n        38:   - Would require traversing AST to find which block contains the target line\n        39:2. Source preservation tests failing\n        40:   - AST reconstruction is not preserving original formatting\n        41:   - Comments and blank lines being lost in some cases\n        42:   - Fundamental limitation: AST doesn't include comments, so reconstruction loses original structure\n        43:3. File-level operations not preserving structure correctly\n        44:   - test_file_level_preservation shows comments being reordered\n        45:   - When using __FILE_START__, comments that appear before imports get moved after\n        46:   - Related to AST reconstruction issue\n        47:Next Steps:\n        48:1. For nested indentation: Would require significant refactoring to:\n        49:   - Parse the AST recursively to find which block contains the target line\n        50:   - Insert at the correct nesting level rather than function level\n        51:   - This is a complex architectural change\n        52:2. For source preservation: Consider alternative approaches:\n        53:   - Use a different parsing strategy that preserves comments\n        54:   - Implement a hybrid approach using both AST and line-based editing\n        55:   - Accept limitations and document them\n        56:Priority: Document current capabilities and limitations. The tool works well for many use cases but has known limitations with nested indentation and comment preservation.\""
