                 {
                  "content": "I've successfully viewed the directory structure and read both the README.md and work_order.txt files. Here's a summary of what I found:\n\n## Directory Structure\nThe project is a Python library called \"bots\" that provides a structured interface for working with LLM agents. It contains:\n- Core bot implementations in `bots/`\n- Tools for code manipulation in `bots/tools/`\n- Tests in `tests/` and `issue103/`\n- Examples and experiments\n- Documentation files\n\n## README.md Summary\nThe bots library provides:\n1. A unified interface for working with different LLM services (OpenAI, Anthropic)\n2. Automatic function-to-tool conversion\n3. Tree-based conversation management with branching\n4. Functional prompting patterns\n5. Pre-built code tools\n6. An Auto Terminal for interactive use\n7. A Lazy Decorator for runtime code generation\n\n## work_order.txt Summary\nThis file documents the implementation status of `python_edit.py`:\n- **Current Status**: 37 tests passing, 6 failing\n- **Completed**: Basic tokenization, comment handling, line insertion, scope-based insertion\n- **Remaining Issues**:\n  1. Nested indentation for line insertion\n  2. Source preservation (AST reconstruction losing formatting)\n  3. File-level operations not preserving structure correctly\n- **Next Steps**: Document limitations and consider alternative approaches for the remaining issues\n\nThe work order indicates that the python_edit.py tool is mostly functional but has some limitations with nested indentation and preserving original source formatting when using AST reconstruction.",
