ld nodes and inserts after them\n        34:Remaining Issues:\n        35:1. Nested indentation for line insertion (test_line_insert_indentation)\n        36:   - When inserting after a line inside nested blocks (if/for/while)\n        37:   - Currently inserts at function level, not at the correct nesting level\n        38:   - Would require traversing AST to find which block contains the target line\n        39:2. Source preservation tests failing\n        40:   - AST reconstruction is not preserving original formatting\n        41:   - Comments and blank lines being lost in some cases\n        42:   - Fundamental limitation: AST doesn't include comments, so reconstruction loses original structure\n        43:3. File-level operations not preserving structure correctly\n        44:   - test_file_level_preservation shows comments being reordered\n        45:   - When using __FILE_START__, comments that appear before imports get moved after\n        46:   - Related to AST reconstruction issue\n        47:Next Steps:\n        48:1. For nested indentation: Would require significant refactoring to:\n        49:   - Parse the AST recursively to find which block contains the target line\n        50:   - Insert at the correct nesting level rather than function level\n        51:   - This is a complex architectural change\n        52:2. For source preservation: Consider alternative approaches:\n        53:   - Use a different parsing strategy that preserves comments\n        54:   - Implement a hybrid approach using both AST and line-based editing\n        55:   - Accept limitations and document them\n        56:Priority: Document current capabilities and limitations. The tool works well for many use cases but has known limitations with nested indentation and comment preservation.\""
