es now works\n              - Can insert code after comments\n              - Preserves indentation at function level\n              - Handles tokenized content correctly\n              - NOW WORKS: Correctly maintains indentation in nested blocks (if/for/while)\n            - Scope-based insertion now works\n              - Can insert after 'OuterClass::another_method' when editing 'OuterClass'\n              - Properly finds child nodes and inserts after them\n            Remaining Issues:\n            1. Source preservation tests failing (5 tests)\n               - AST reconstruction is not preserving original formatting\n               - Comments and blank lines being lost in some cases\n               - Fundamental limitation: AST doesn't include comments, so reconstruction loses original structure\n               - Affected tests:\n                 - test_line_insert_ast_handling\n                 - test_line_insert_function_body\n                 - test_source_preservation\n                 - test_ast_tree_preservation\n                 - test_file_level_preservation\n            2. File-level operations not preserving structure correctly\n               - test_file_level_preservation shows comments being reordered\n               - When using __FILE_START__, comments that appear before imports get moved after\n               - Related to AST reconstruction issue\n            Next Steps:\n            1. For source preservation: Consider alternative approaches:\n               - Use a different parsing strategy that preserves comments (e.g., lib2to3, parso)\n               - Implement a hybrid approach using both AST and line-based editing\n               - Accept limitations and document them\n            Priority: Document current capabilities and limitations. The tool works well for many use cases including nested indentation, but has known limitations with comment preservation during AST reconstruction."
