                                                                                                                                                                                              "content": "Yes! Great idea! Python does support multiple statements on a single line using semicolons. So we could have:\n\n```python\nx = 1; \"\"\";;;comment;;;\"\"\"\n```\n\nThis would be valid Python syntax. Let me update the tokenization to use this approach:",
